Class JarLauncher

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.messaging.broadcasters.Multicaster
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.messaging.repeaters.BaseRepeater
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.resource.resources.jar.launcher.JarLauncher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Receiver<Transmittable>, Transmitter<Transmittable>, NamedObject, PackagePathed, Broadcaster, Listener, Repeater, Transceiver
    public class JarLauncher
extends BaseRepeater
    Launches an executable Java program from a jar Resource, in a child or detached process. The process type and program arguments are passed as parameters to the constructor. Any number of Resourced objects can be added with source(Resourced). The method run() then launches the application, attempting to use each Resource that was added with source(Resourced) in order.
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
